    "content": "Hargeisa, Somaliland – Saleban Mahmud Adan formally resigned as Speaker of the House of Elders (Guurti) on Wednesday, ending his tenure as head of the upper house of parliament. The resignation was announced during a session attended by members of the Guurti and senior government officials.\n\nAdan, a veteran politician, had held the position since 2017. Sources indicate his decision came amid growing pressure from within the Guurti over differences regarding the chamber's role in ongoing political negotiations. The House of Elders has been a key institution in Somaliland's stability, often mediating disputes between the executive and lower house.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, which maintains close ties to Somaliland's political developments, this shift signals potential changes in the balance of power. Diaspora communities have historically played a role in funding political campaigns and advocating for Somaliland's recognition. The appointment of a new speaker will be closely watched by those monitoring reconciliation efforts.\n\nThe resignation leaves a leadership vacuum that the Guurti must fill in accordance with its internal procedures. Analysts suggest the move could either calm tensions or trigger further realignments ahead of scheduled elections. \n\nRead the original report from Horseed Media here: https://horseedmedia.net/guddoomiyihii-guurtida-somaliland-oo-xilka-wareejiyey/423646/",
